---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

const testimonials = [
  {
    name: 'Stephen Attenborough',
    title: 'Virgin Galactic founding employee, former Commercial Director & Chief Customer Officer; Virgin Unite trustee & Board Director',
    quoteBefore: '\u201cOur ambition for partnerships at Virgin Galactic was simple \u2014 we wanted to work with a brand that shared our DNA for exploration and ',
    quoteHighlight: 'pioneering spirit',
    quoteAfter: '. Laura Wood was the driving force that made that vision a reality in the partnership between Virgin Galactic and JLR.\u201d',
    image: `${base}stephen-carousel.webp`,
    mobileImage: `${base}stephen-mobile.jpg`,
    paragraphs: [
      '\u201cOur ambition for partnerships at Virgin Galactic was simple \u2014 we wanted it to go further than a sponsorship; we wanted to work with a brand that shared our DNA for exploration and pioneering spirit. Laura Wood was the driving force that made that vision a reality in the partnership between Virgin Galactic and JLR.',
      'Working with Laura was a masterclass in how to manage a partnership of this scale. She was responsible for weaving Land Rover into the very fabric of our operations \u2014 from the fleet of vehicles that towed our spaceships to the runway, to the high-stakes activations that brought our future astronauts together. She never saw it as a simple branding exercise; she understood that every touchpoint had to feel authentic to the mission.',
      'What sets Laura apart is her ability to navigate the complexities of two massive global brands while never losing sight of the creative goal. She is incredibly sharp, operationally fearless, and has an innate sense of how to tell a story that resonates globally.',
      'Laura is one of those rare leaders who can handle the minute details of a technical integration one moment and the strategic demands of a world-first launch the next, all while keeping her team focused and inspired. It was a privilege to have her at the helm during such a defining chapter for the world\u2019s first commercial spaceline.\u201d',
    ],
    image2: '',
    images: [`${base}stephen-1.webp`, `${base}stephen-2.webp`, `${base}stephen-3.webp`, `${base}stephen-4.webp`],
  },
  {
    name: 'Stephanie Wenborn',
    title: 'Head of Marketing & Partnerships, EON',
    quoteBefore: '\u201cTrust and shared vision are the bedrock of any great partnership. Our history with Laura spans three Bond films \u2014 Skyfall, Spectre and No Time To Die \u2014 and that track record made Beyond The Badge the obvious choice for our current and future projects at EON. Laura has an incredible intuition for connecting the right brands with the right ',
    quoteHighlight: 'cultural moments',
    quoteAfter: '.\u201d',
    image: `${base}wenborn-carousel.webp`,
    mobileImage: `${base}wenborn-mobile.jpg`,
    paragraphs: [
      '\u201cTrust and shared vision are the bedrock of any great partnership. Our history with Laura spans three Bond films (Skyfall, Spectre and No Time To Die), and that track record made Beyond The Badge the obvious choice for our current and future projects at EON.',
      'Laura has an incredible intuition for connecting the right brands with the right cultural moments and we\u2019re excited to keep building on this legacy together.\u201d',
    ],
    image2: '',
    images: [`${base}wenborn-1.webp`, `${base}wenborn-2.webp`, `${base}wenborn-3.webp`, `${base}wenborn-4.webp`, `${base}wenborn-5.webp`],
  },
  {
    name: 'Dominic Reid OBE',
    title: 'Formerly Founding CEO of the Invictus Games',
    quoteBefore: '\u201cLaura has an intelligent and imaginative grasp of the way brands can work with properties that they sponsor to their mutual benefit. She was instrumental in the successful ',
    quoteHighlight: 'partnership',
    quoteAfter: ' between Jaguar Land Rover and the Invictus Games. And she brought to bear her creativity and incisiveness to address challenges and deliver better and better solutions. In addition to this, she is a delight to work with.\u201d',
    image: `${base}testimonial-2.jpg`,
    mobileImage: `${base}dominic-mobile.jpg`,
    paragraphs: [
      '\u201cLaura has an intelligent and imaginative grasp of the way brands can work with properties that they sponsor to their mutual benefit.',
      'She was instrumental in the successful partnership between Jaguar Land Rover and the Invictus Games. And she brought to bear her creativity and incisiveness to address challenges and deliver better and better solutions. In addition to this, she is a delight to work with.\u201d',
    ],
    image2: '',
    images: [`${base}dominic-1.webp`, `${base}dominic-2.webp`, `${base}dominic-3.webp`, `${base}dominic-4.webp`],
  },
  {
    name: 'Niamh Bryne',
    title: 'Artist Manager \u2014 Gorillaz, Founder Eleven Management & MMF Chair',
    quoteBefore: '\u201cWhen we first sat down with Laura Wood and her team at Jaguar Land Rover, we knew we weren\u2019t looking at a standard corporate partnership. Laura didn\u2019t just want a logo on a car; she had the vision to treat our Gorillaz fanbase as a ',
    quoteHighlight: 'community of untapped talent',
    quoteAfter: '.\u201d',
    image: `${base}testimonial-1.jpg`,
    mobileImage: `${base}niamh-mobile.jpg`,
    paragraphs: [
      '\u201cWhen we first sat down with Laura Wood and her team at Jaguar Land Rover, we weren\u2019t looking at a standard corporate partnership. Laura didn\u2019t just want a logo on a car; she had the vision to treat our Gorillaz fanbase as a community of untapped talent.',
      'With a brief to promote the brand new Jaguar Formula E Race team \u2014 to plug a vital skills gap and find the next generation of world-class software engineers \u2014 we had to access that community where they were in culture.',
      'Together, we created a high-stakes code-cracking challenge within Noodle\u2019s virtual garage in the Gorillaz app, turning addressing a vital skills gap into a progressive, immersive gaming experience.',
      '400,000 app downloads, 41,000 entries, 500 code crackers and a team of next-gen cyber engineers recruited \u2014 the results speak to her ability to lead complex, multi-faceted projects across global brands.',
      'Beyond the metrics, Laura\u2019s leadership ensured that the creative integrity of the Gorillaz universe remained intact while successfully launching the Jaguar Formula E Race team into a new era.',
      'Laura didn\u2019t just fill a recruitment quota; she created a blueprint for how brands should engage with the future of tech. It was a rare, progressive and exciting venture that wouldn\u2019t have happened without her drive.\u201d',
    ],
    image2: '',
    images: [`${base}niamh-1.jpg`, `${base}niamh-2.jpg`, `${base}niamh-3.jpg`],
  },
  {
    name: 'David Gandy',
    title: 'Model & Entrepreneur',
    quoteBefore: '\u201cI have had the pleasure of working with Laura for over 15 years on high-profile events, activations, and partnerships. Throughout this time, I cannot speak highly enough about her unwavering commitment, dedication, and exceptional problem-solving skills. She is never shy of thinking outside the box, and her dynamic, innovative approach has been instrumental in driving the huge successes achieved with the brands she has worked with.\u201d',
    quoteHighlight: '',
    quoteAfter: '',
    image: `${base}testimonial-4.jpg`,
    mobileImage: `${base}gandy-mobile.jpg`,
    paragraphs: [
      '\u201cI have had the pleasure of working with Laura for over 15 years on high-profile events, activations, and partnerships. Throughout this time, I cannot speak highly enough about her unwavering commitment, dedication, and exceptional problem-solving skills. She is never shy of thinking outside the box, and her dynamic, innovative approach has been instrumental in driving the huge successes achieved with the brands she has worked with.',
      'On a personal level, Laura is one of the kindest, most thoughtful, and considerate people I have ever had the pleasure to meet and work with. Her professionalism combined with her genuine kindness makes her an invaluable partner in any project.\u201d',
    ],
    image2: '',
    images: [`${base}gandy-1.webp`, `${base}gandy-2.webp`],
  },
  {
    name: 'Paul Amadi MBE',
    title: 'Marketing Consultant (former British Red Cross Executive Director of Marketing, Fundraising and Communications)',
    quoteBefore: '\u201cWorking with Laura on the Jaguar Land Rover \u2014 British Red Cross partnership was an 8-year demonstration of strategic insight, dynamism, and an exemplary commitment to ',
    quoteHighlight: 'partnership working',
    quoteAfter: '.\u201d',
    image: `${base}testimonial-5.jpg`,
    mobileImage: `${base}amadi-mobile.jpg`,
    paragraphs: [
      '\u201cWorking with Laura on the Jaguar Land Rover \u2014 British Red Cross charity brand partnership was an 8-year demonstration of strategic insight, dynamism, an exemplary commitment to partnership working and the recognition of the importance of value alignment, all of which (and more) Laura provided on a daily basis.',
      'A key driver to her success was that Laura always saw herself as the custodian of a long-established partnership which had the capability to achieve increasing cut through.',
      'As the brand lead for the British Red Cross, our joint strategic challenge was to evolve a 70-year partnership and take it from an established alliance into something progressive and modern \u2014 a genuine engine for driving real humanitarian impact.',
      'Laura\u2019s input transformed what could be characterised as a disparate partnership into something which focused on the one area where we could truly make an impact: Disaster Relief.',
      'The defining element of disaster relief is the ability to move at pace, creating immediate impact. One of the many successes enabled by Laura\u2019s leadership was the mobilisation of a fleet of brand-new Defenders to work on the front line of the British Red Cross\u2019s Covid response.',
      'Underpinning all of the strategic and evidence-based insight Laura provided was a manifest commitment to the values of the British Red Cross, successfully combined with the need to drive purpose visibility for JLR customers and employees.\u201d',
    ],
    image2: '',
    images: [`${base}amadi-1.webp`, `${base}amadi-2.webp`, `${base}amadi-3.webp`],
  },
  {
    name: 'Dave Benett',
    title: 'Photographer (Getty Images / London Evening Standard)',
    quoteBefore: '\u201cIn my line of work, you see a lot of people who try to \u2018manage\u2019 the room, but Laura Wood is one of the rare few who actually understands the energy of it. Simply put, Laura curates cultural moments that ',
    quoteHighlight: 'matter',
    quoteAfter: '.\u201d',
    image: `${base}testimonial-3.jpg`,
    mobileImage: `${base}benett-mobile.jpg`,
    paragraphs: [
      '\u201cIn my line of work, you see a lot of people who try to \u2018manage\u2019 the room, but Laura Wood is one of the rare few who actually understands the energy of it. We\u2019ve worked together across countless high-profile events and launches over two incredible decades \u2014 from cutting her teeth with her agency Golden Goose PR to becoming a globally respected director at JLR.',
      'Laura has that rare combination of professional steel and genuine warmth. She understands that the perfect shot isn\u2019t just about the person in front of the lens; it\u2019s about the atmosphere, the timing, and the narrative she\u2019s spent months building behind the scenes.',
      'Simply put, Laura curates cultural moments that matter. Her ability to handle big personalities and even bigger brand expectations with such grace is why she\u2019s so respected in this industry. Whenever Laura is running the show, you just know the end result is going to look world-class and, more importantly, people are actually going to be talking about it. She\u2019s a class act, sharp, professional, and someone who genuinely understands the intersection of brand and culture.\u201d',
    ],
    image2: '',
    images: [`${base}benett-1.webp`],
  },
];

// Serialised subset for the full-story modal JS
const storiesData = testimonials.map(t => ({
  name:       t.name,
  title:      t.title,
  paragraphs: t.paragraphs,
  // images[] drives the modal image slots; falls back to the single sidebar portrait
  images:     ((t as any).images as string[]) ?? [t.image],
}));
---

<!-- Outer scroll track: 625vh default (5 collapsed slots × ~125vh each); expanded to 875vh via JS (7 slots × ~125vh each) -->
<div class="testimonials-track" id="testimonials">
  <!-- Sticky panel: pins to viewport while track scrolls past -->
  <section class="testimonials-sticky" aria-label="What our friends say">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="testimonials__header">
        <h2 class="testimonials__heading">What our friends say</h2>
      </div>

      <hr class="testimonials__rule" />

      <div class="testimonials__body">

        <!-- Left: name list -->
        <div class="testimonials__names">
          {testimonials.slice(0, 5).map((t, i) => (
            <button
              type="button"
              class={`t-name-btn${i === 0 ? ' is-active' : ''}`}
              data-index={String(i)}
            >
              <span class="t-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
              <span class="t-name-text">{t.name}</span>
            </button>
          ))}

          <div class="t-names-extra" id="t-names-extra" aria-hidden="true">
            {testimonials.slice(5).map((t, i) => (
              <button
                type="button"
                class="t-name-btn"
                data-index={String(i + 5)}
              >
                <span class="t-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
                <span class="t-name-text">{t.name}</span>
              </button>
            ))}
          </div>

          <button type="button" class="t-more-btn" id="t-more-btn" aria-expanded="false">
            <span class="t-more-line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="t-more-text">More voices</span>
          </button>
        </div>

        <!-- Centre: portrait (position:absolute crossfade) -->
        <div class="testimonials__photo-stage">
          {testimonials.map((t, i) => (
            <div class={`t-photo${i === 0 ? ' is-active' : ''}`} data-index={String(i)}>
          <img class="t-photo__img--desktop" src={t.image} alt={t.name} />
              <img class="t-photo__img--mobile" src={(t as any).mobileImage} alt={t.name} loading="lazy" />
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <!-- Right: quote (position:absolute crossfade) -->
        <div class="testimonials__quote-stage">
          {testimonials.map((t, i) => (
            <div class={`t-quote${i === 0 ? ' is-active' : ''}`} data-index={String(i)}>
              <blockquote>
                {t.quoteBefore}<em class="t-highlight">{t.quoteHighlight}</em>{t.quoteAfter}
                {t.quoteParagraph2 && (
                  <span class="t-quote-p2">{t.quoteParagraph2}</span>
                )}
              </blockquote>
              <p class="t-role-credit">{t.title}</p>
              <footer class="t-attribution">
                <strong class="t-client-name">{t.name}</strong>
                <span class="t-client-role">{t.title}</span>
              </footer>
              {(i === 1 || i === 3 || i === 5) ? (
                <div class="t-btn-row">
                  <button type="button" class="t-story-btn">
                    <span class="t-story-btn__text">The Full Story +</span>
                  </button>
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="t-play-btn"
                    data-video-webm={
                      i === 1 ? `${base}wenborn-campaign.webm` :
                      i === 5 ? ''                              :
                                `${base}campaign-video.webm`
                    }
                    data-video-mp4={
                      i === 1 ? `${base}wenborn-campaign.mp4` :
                      i === 5 ? `${base}amadi-campaign.mp4`   :
                                `${base}campaign-video.mp4`
                    }
                    aria-label={
                      i === 1 ? 'Play EON Bond film campaign video' :
                      i === 5 ? 'Play JLR — British Red Cross campaign video' :
                                'Play Gorillaz × Jaguar Land Rover campaign video'
                    }
                  >
                    <span class="t-play-btn__text">Play Campaign</span>
                    <span class="t-play-btn__icon" aria-hidden="true">▶</span>
                  </button>
                </div>
              ) : (
                <button type="button" class="t-story-btn">
                  <span class="t-story-btn__text">The Full Story +</span>
                </button>
              )}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<!-- Campaign video modal — shared by Stephanie Wenborn and Niamh Bryne -->
<div class="t-video-modal" id="t-video-modal" aria-hidden="true" role="dialog" aria-label="Campaign video">
  <div class="t-video-modal__backdrop" id="t-video-modal-backdrop"></div>
  <div class="t-video-modal__container">
    <button class="t-video-modal__close" id="t-video-modal-close" aria-label="Close video">✕ Close</button>
    <div class="t-video-modal__video-wrap">
      <video
        id="t-campaign-video"
        controls
        playsinline
        preload="none"
        aria-label="Campaign video"
      >
        <!-- src attributes are set dynamically by JS from the clicked play button's data-video-* attrs -->
        <source id="t-campaign-src-webm" src="" type="video/webm" />
        <source id="t-campaign-src-mp4"  src="" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Full-story data for JS (not rendered) -->
<script type="application/json" id="t-stories-data" set:html={JSON.stringify(storiesData)} />

<!-- Full-story modal -->
<div class="t-fs-modal" id="t-fs-modal" aria-hidden="true" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-label="Full story">
  <div class="t-fs-overlay" id="t-fs-overlay"></div>
  <button type="button" class="t-fs-close" id="t-fs-close">✕ Close</button>
  <!-- Full-story modal panel (single scroll container) -->
  <div class="t-fs-panel" data-lenis-prevent>
    <!-- B watermark image — bleeds from top-right of the panel -->
    <img class="t-fs-watermark" src="/b-logo-watermark.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
    <div class="t-fs-body">
      <!-- Left: role + images -->
      <div class="t-fs-left">
        <p class="t-fs-name" id="t-fs-name"></p>
        <p class="t-fs-role" id="t-fs-role"></p>
        <div class="t-fs-images">
          <div class="t-fs-img-wrap" id="t-fs-img1-wrap">
            <img class="t-fs-img" id="t-fs-img1" src="" alt="" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="t-fs-img-wrap" id="t-fs-img2-wrap">
            <img class="t-fs-img" id="t-fs-img2" src="" alt="" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="t-fs-img-wrap" id="t-fs-img3-wrap">
            <img class="t-fs-img" id="t-fs-img3" src="" alt="" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="t-fs-img-wrap" id="t-fs-img4-wrap">
            <img class="t-fs-img" id="t-fs-img4" src="" alt="" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="t-fs-img-wrap" id="t-fs-img5-wrap">
            <img class="t-fs-img" id="t-fs-img5" src="" alt="" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Right: full quote -->
      <div class="t-fs-right" id="t-fs-right">
        <div class="t-fs-quote" id="t-fs-quote"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<style>
  /* ─── Scroll track (outer, 300vh) ─── */
  .testimonials-track {
    height: 625vh;
    background: transparent;
    /* Needed so sticky child has correct offset parent */
    position: relative;
  }

  /* Sticky panel (pins while track scrolls) */
  .testimonials-sticky {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    height: 100vh;
    background: transparent;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    /* overflow:clip — clips visual overflow exactly like overflow:hidden but does
       NOT create a scroll container. overflow:hidden would cause Lenis to detect
       this as a scrollable element, yield wheel-event control, and break smooth
       scroll over the entire testimonials section. */
    overflow: clip;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  .testimonials-sticky .container {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .testimonials__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-variation-settings: normal;
    font-size: var(--font-size-label);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #052715;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }

  .testimonials__rule {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid #D9D0C8;
    margin: 0 0 52px;
  }

  /* ─── Three-column grid ─── */
  .testimonials__body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(100px, 12.7%) minmax(180px, 26%) 1fr;
    gap: 0 clamp(32px, 5vw, 72px);
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* ─── Left: name list ─── */
  .testimonials__names {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .t-name-btn {
    position: relative;
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 8px 0;
    border: none;                  /* reset browser UA button border */
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: #BBB1A7;
    text-align: left;
    cursor: pointer;
    background: none;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    transition: color 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1),
                font-weight 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1);
  }

  .t-name-btn.is-active,
  .t-name-btn:hover {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #004f26;
  }

  /* Arrow — absolute at left:0, fades in after slide begins */
  .t-arrow {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    color: #004f26;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.4s ease 0.1s;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .t-name-btn.is-active .t-arrow,
  .t-name-btn:hover .t-arrow {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  /* Name text — slides right */
  .t-name-text {
    display: inline-block;
    transform: translateX(0);
    transition: transform 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1);
  }

  .t-name-btn.is-active .t-name-text,
  .t-name-btn:hover .t-name-text {
    transform: translateX(28px);
  }

  /* ─── Centre: photo stage ─── */
  .testimonials__photo-stage {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
  }

  .t-photo {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: scale(1.04);
    transition:
      opacity 0.75s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94),
      transform 0.75s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94);
    will-change: opacity, transform;
  }

  .t-photo.is-active {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: scale(1);
  }

  .t-photo img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: top center;
    filter: none;
    display: block;
  }

  /* Mobile-specific portrait — hidden above 390px.
     Uses img.class to match specificity of the .t-photo img rule above. */
  .t-photo img.t-photo__img--mobile { display: none; }

  /* ─── Right: quote stage ─── */
  .testimonials__quote-stage {
    position: relative;
    /* Bleed to the right page margin — cancels the container's right padding */
    margin-right: calc(-1 * var(--section-padding-x));
    /* Explicit height so position:absolute quotes have a containing block
       and the stage never reflows when switching testimonials. */
    height: clamp(360px, 46vh, 540px);
    /* Chrome: touch-action:manipulation on the stage means the browser fires
       click on child buttons without gesture-based suppression, even when the
       parent .testimonials-sticky has touchstart/touchend listeners. */
    touch-action: manipulation;
  }

  .t-quote {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease;
  }

  .t-quote.is-active {
    opacity: 1;
    pointer-events: auto;
    /* Stay position:absolute — switching active quote must NOT change
       the stage height or the whole panel would recenter and jump. */
  }

  .t-quote blockquote {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 55px;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    font-style: normal;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    /* Clamp to 6 lines for mobile / reduced-motion / no-JS paths */
    display: -webkit-box;
    -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
    -webkit-line-clamp: 6;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .t-highlight {
    font-style: inherit;
    font-weight: inherit;
    color: inherit;
  }

  /* Second paragraph of a multi-paragraph quote */
  .t-quote-p2 {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 1em;
  }

  .t-attribution {
    display: none;
  }

  /* Credit line: role shown below quote with paragraph-break spacing */
  .t-role-credit {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-variation-settings: normal;
    font-size: var(--font-size-label);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #BBB1A7;
    margin: 28px 0 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .t-client-name {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
  }

  .t-client-role {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-variation-settings: normal;
    font-size: var(--font-size-label);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* ─── Mobile: scroll-pin ACTIVE, horizontal names, stacked content ─── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    /* Track stays 625vh — JS scroll driver remains active */

    /* Sticky pin stays: do NOT override position/height here */
    .testimonials-sticky {
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 32px 0;
      overflow: clip;
    }

    /* Tighten header so content has room */
    .testimonials__heading { margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .testimonials__rule    { margin-bottom: 48px; }

    /* Body: grid — names full-width, photo left (2fr), quote right (3fr) */
    .testimonials__body {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 2fr 3fr;
      column-gap: 28px;
      row-gap: 0;
    }


    /* ── Names: hidden at mobile; display:contents lets More Voices escape into the grid ── */
    .testimonials__names { display: contents; }

    /* Hide all name buttons and extra-names container */
    .t-name-btn,
    .t-names-extra,
    .t-names-extra.is-open { display: none; }

    /* ── More voices: repositioned below testimonial content ── */
    .t-more-btn {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;  /* span both columns */
      grid-row: 2;          /* below content row */
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 12px;
      margin-top: 24px;
      margin-left: 0;
      padding: 0;
      border-left: none;
      font-size: 14px;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }

    .t-more-line { display: block; width: 32px; }


    /* ── Photo: left column (2fr), top-aligned, portrait ratio ── */
    .testimonials__photo-stage {
      grid-column: 1;
      grid-row: 1;           /* explicit to avoid auto-placement surprises */
      align-self: start;
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      aspect-ratio: 2 / 3;
      overflow: hidden;
      min-height: 180px;
    }

    /* ── Quote stage: right column, min-height sized for 8-line clamp + attribution + CTA ── */
    .testimonials__quote-stage {
      grid-column: 2;
      grid-row: 1;
      position: relative;
      height: auto;
      min-height: 500px;   /* 8 lines × 28px × 1.65 ≈ 370px + attribution + button */
      margin-right: 0;
    }

    /* Quotes: opacity crossfade — keeps elements in DOM so JS can measure offsetTop */
    .t-quote {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      width: 100%;
      opacity: 0;
      pointer-events: none;
      transition: opacity 0.5s ease;
    }

    .t-quote.is-active {
      opacity: 1;
      pointer-events: auto;
    }

    /* 8-line clamp — belt-and-braces alongside late-cascade rule */
    .t-quote blockquote {
      display: -webkit-box;
      -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
      -webkit-line-clamp: 8;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    /* Attribution: show name + role below quote */
    .t-attribution {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 2px;
      margin-top: 16px;   /* more space between quote and attribution */
    }

    /* Hide role-credit — attribution covers both name and role */
    .t-role-credit { display: none; }

    /* Name: Inter, capitalised — same size/colour as role */
    .t-client-name {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-variation-settings: normal;
      font-size: var(--font-size-label);
      font-weight: 400;
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    }

    /* Role: capitalised to match */
    .t-client-role {
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    }

    /* CTA buttons */
    .t-story-btn { margin-top: 20px; }
    .t-btn-row   { margin-top: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }

    /* All 7 testimonials available in the carousel from the start */
    .testimonials-track { height: 875vh !important; } /* 7 slots × 125vh */

    /* Hide More voices / Show fewer — all testimonials are already in the carousel */
    .t-more-btn { display: none !important; }
  }
  /* ─── PLAY CAMPAIGN button (testimonial 0 only) ─── */
  .t-play-btn {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-variation-settings: normal;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    background: #052715;
    border: 1px solid #052715;
    padding: 14px 24px;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
    isolation: isolate;
    transition:
      color 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94),
      letter-spacing 0.4s ease,
      border-color 0.4s ease;
  }

  /* Cream fill that wipes in from left on hover */
  .t-play-btn::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: var(--color-cream);
    clip-path: inset(0 100% 0 0);
    transition: clip-path 0.55s cubic-bezier(0.76, 0, 0.24, 1);
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .t-play-btn__text,
  .t-play-btn__icon {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .t-play-btn__icon {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
  }

  .t-play-btn:hover::before {
    clip-path: inset(0 0% 0 0);
  }

  .t-play-btn:hover {
    color: #052715;
    letter-spacing: 0.11em;
    border-color: #052715;
  }

  /* ─── Video modal ─── */
  .t-video-modal {
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 10000;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    transition: opacity 0.35s ease;
  }

  .t-video-modal.is-open {
    opacity: 1;
    pointer-events: auto;
  }

  .t-video-modal__backdrop {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0, 13, 7, 0.88);
    cursor: pointer;
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  }

  .t-video-modal__container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    width: min(90vw, 1400px);
  }

  .t-video-modal__close {
    position: absolute;
    top: -44px;
    right: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-variation-settings: normal;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(232, 224, 212, 0.6);
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 8px 0;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .t-video-modal__close:hover {
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .t-video-modal__video-wrap {
    position: relative;
    background: #000;
  }

  .t-video-modal__video-wrap video {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    border: none;
  }

  /* ── 1440px: proportional scale-down from 1522px baseline ─── */
  @media (max-width: 1440px) {
    /* padding-top removed — centering handled by justify-content: center */
    /* Do NOT reduce stage height — blockquote is already at 28px so there is
       less text; shrinking the stage too would leave no room for the absolutely-
       positioned play button at bottom: 0 */
    .testimonials__quote-stage {
      height: clamp(410px, 50vh, 570px);  /* midpoint between too-close and too-far */
      margin-right: 0;  /* remove screen-edge bleed — aligns with container and divider */
    }
    /* Target blockquote directly — it has explicit 32px/55px so inherited values
       from .t-quote would be silently overridden without this specificity */
    .t-quote blockquote {
      font-size: 28px;    /* 32px reduced further at user request */
      line-height: 48px;  /* maintains ×1.71 ratio */
    }
    .t-name-btn {
      font-size: 22px;  /* 24px × 0.917 */
    }
    .t-video-modal__container {
      width: min(85vw, 1200px);  /* scales down from baseline min(90vw, 1400px) */
    }
  }

  /* ── 1280px: proportional scale-down from 1440px ─── */
  @media (max-width: 1280px) {
    /* padding-top removed — centering handled by justify-content: center */
    .testimonials__quote-stage {
      height: clamp(369px, 45vh, 513px);  /* clamp(410,50vh,570) × 0.90 */
    }
    .t-quote blockquote {
      font-size: 26px;    /* 28px × 0.929 */
      line-height: 43px;  /* 48px × 0.90 */
    }
    .t-name-btn {
      font-size: 21px;  /* 22px × 0.955 */
    }
    .t-video-modal__container {
      width: min(85vw, 1100px);  /* scales down from 1200px */
    }
    /* Stage becomes tight — switch play button to normal flow */
    .t-play-btn {
      position: relative;
      bottom: auto;
      left: auto;
      margin-top: 24px;
      display: inline-flex;
    }
    /* Inside the row, play button inherits no extra margin from above */
    .t-btn-row .t-play-btn { margin-top: 0; }
    /* .t-story-btn and .t-btn-row are already in normal flow — no override needed */
    .t-more-btn  { font-size: 16px; }   /* 18px × 0.889 — scales with .t-name-btn */
    .t-more-line { width: 24px; }       /* 48px − 24px — proportional reduction */
  }

  /* ── 1024px: proportional scale-down from 1280px ─── */
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .testimonials__quote-stage {
      height: clamp(332px, 40.5vh, 462px);
    }
    .t-quote blockquote {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 36px;
    }
    .t-name-btn {
      font-size: 20px;
    }
    .t-video-modal__container {
      width: min(85vw, 990px);
    }
    /* .t-play-btn already handled by ≤1280px breakpoint above — no override needed */
    .t-more-btn  { font-size: 15px; }   /* 16px × 0.938 — keeps pace with .t-name-btn → 20px */
    /* .t-more-line stays 24px — no further reduction needed at this breakpoint */
  }

  /* ─── "3 more voices" toggle button ─── */
  .t-more-btn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-end;
    gap: 12px;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    margin-top: 24px;
    padding: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-script);
    font-style: italic;
    font-variation-settings: "wght" 500, "hght" 1000;
    font-size: 18px;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: #BBB1A7;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .t-more-btn:hover {
    color: #004f26;
  }

  /* Horizontal line — replaces arrow, aligns to text bottom */
  .t-more-line {
    display: block;
    width: 48px;
    height: 0.5px;
    background: currentColor;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-bottom: 4px; /* fine-tune optical baseline alignment */
  }

  /* ─── Hidden extra names container ─── */
  .t-names-extra {
    overflow: hidden;
    max-height: 0;
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none; /* prevent keyboard/click interaction with hidden names */
    transition:
      max-height 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94),
      opacity 0.4s ease;
  }

  .t-names-extra.is-open {
    max-height: 400px;
    opacity: 1;
    pointer-events: auto;
  }

  /* Individual extra names: slide + fade in; restore full transition set from base rule */
  .t-names-extra .t-name-btn {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(-6px);
    transition:
      color 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1),
      font-weight 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1),
      opacity 0.4s ease,
      transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94);
  }

  .t-names-extra.is-open .t-name-btn { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  .t-names-extra.is-open .t-name-btn:nth-child(1) { transition-delay: 0.06s; }
  .t-names-extra.is-open .t-name-btn:nth-child(2) { transition-delay: 0.12s; }
  .t-names-extra.is-open .t-name-btn:nth-child(3) { transition-delay: 0.18s; }

  /* ─── "The Full Story +" CTA button ─── */
  .t-story-btn {
    /* In normal flow — always sits a fixed gap below the attribution, regardless of quote length */
    position: relative;       /* contains ::before so the hover fill stays within the button */
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    margin-top: 40px;
    /* iOS: suppress click-delay and prevent parent touchstart listener from swallowing the tap */
    touch-action: manipulation;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-variation-settings: normal;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #052715;
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid #052715;
    padding: 14px 24px;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
    isolation: isolate;
    transition:
      color 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94),
      letter-spacing 0.4s ease;
  }

  /* Dark green fill wipes in from left on hover */
  .t-story-btn::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: #052715;
    clip-path: inset(0 100% 0 0);
    transition: clip-path 0.55s cubic-bezier(0.76, 0, 0.24, 1);
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .t-story-btn__text {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .t-story-btn:hover::before { clip-path: inset(0 0% 0 0); }
  .t-story-btn:hover {
    color: var(--color-cream);
    letter-spacing: 0.11em;
  }

  /* ─── Button row — first testimonial only: side-by-side layout ─── */
  .t-btn-row {
    /* In normal flow — sits below the attribution like the standalone story button */
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 40px;
  }
  /* Play button resets its own absolute positioning when inside the row */
  .t-btn-row .t-play-btn {
    position: relative;
    bottom: auto;
    left: auto;
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  /* Story button's margin-top already 0 inside the row (row handles spacing) */
  .t-btn-row .t-story-btn {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  /* ═══ Full-story modal ═══════════════════════════════════════════ */
  .t-fs-modal {
    position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 10002;
    visibility: hidden; pointer-events: none;
  }
  .t-fs-modal.is-open { visibility: visible; pointer-events: auto; }
  .t-fs-overlay {
    position: absolute; inset: 0;
    background: #052715;
    /* opacity is driven by GSAP — no CSS transition here */
  }
  .t-fs-close {
    position: absolute;
    top: 18px;
    right: var(--section-padding-x, 48px);
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-variation-settings: normal;
    font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
    background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer;
    padding: 8px 0;
    z-index: 1; transition: color 0.2s ease;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .t-fs-close:hover { color: #ffffff; }
  .t-fs-panel {
    position: absolute;
    top: 64px;
    left: var(--section-padding-x, 48px);
    right: var(--section-padding-x, 48px);
    bottom: 0;
    background: var(--color-cream, #f8f2ed);
    /* Panel is the single scroll container — both columns scroll together */
    overflow-y: auto;
    overflow-x: hidden;
    /* transform, opacity and transitions are driven by GSAP */
    will-change: transform, opacity;
  }
  .t-fs-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 3fr;
    /* No explicit row height — grid grows to natural content height so both
       columns size to their tallest child, giving a unified scroll experience */
    padding-top: 96px;
    padding-bottom: 96px;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }
  .t-fs-left {
    /* Normal flow — no independent scroll */
    padding: clamp(28px,3.5vw,64px);
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
  }
  .t-fs-watermark {
    position: absolute;
    top: 32px;
    left: -150px;
    width: clamp(420px, 55vw, 780px);
    height: auto;
    opacity: 0.045;
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
    pointer-events: none;
    user-select: none;
    -webkit-user-select: none;
    z-index: 0;
    display: block;
  }
  .t-fs-name {
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-variation-settings: normal;
    font-size: var(--font-size-label, 0.7rem); font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #BBB1A7; line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 4px;
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .t-fs-role {
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-variation-settings: normal;
    font-size: var(--font-size-label, 0.7rem); font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #BBB1A7; line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 clamp(44px,calc(2.5vw + 24px),60px);
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .t-fs-images {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    gap: 32px;
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
  }
  .t-fs-img-wrap {
    width: 100%; overflow: hidden;
    background: rgba(5,39,21,0.07);
  }
  .t-fs-img {
    width: 100%; height: auto;
    object-fit: cover; object-position: center top;
    display: block;
  }
  .t-fs-img[src=""] { display: none; }
  .t-fs-right {
    /* Right column — normal flow, scrolls with the panel */
    padding: clamp(28px,4vw,72px) clamp(28px,4.5vw,72px) clamp(40px,5vw,80px);
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }
  :global(.t-fs-quote p) {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 400; line-height: 50px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em; color: #052715;
    margin: 0 0 1.5em;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  :global(.t-fs-quote p:last-child) { margin-bottom: 0; }

  /* ─── Late-cascade 768px: wins over 1440/1280/1024px blocks above ─── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .t-quote blockquote {
      display: -webkit-box;      /* required for -webkit-line-clamp */
      -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
      -webkit-line-clamp: 8;     /* truncate at 8 lines with ellipsis */
      overflow: hidden;
      font-size: 28px !important;
      line-height: 1.65;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .t-name-btn,
    .t-names-extra,
    .t-names-extra.is-open { display: none; }
    .t-more-btn {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
      grid-row: 2;
      display: flex;
      margin-top: 24px;
      margin-left: 0;
      padding: 0;
      border-left: none;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    /* Grid placement overrides */
    .testimonials__photo-stage {
      grid-column: 1;
      grid-row: 1;
      align-self: start;
      height: auto;
      width: 100%;
      aspect-ratio: 2 / 3;
      min-height: 180px;
    }
    .testimonials__quote-stage {
      grid-column: 2;
      grid-row: 1;
      height: auto;
      min-height: 500px;
      width: 100%;
    }
    /* Quotes: opacity crossfade — elements stay in DOM for JS line-reveal measurement */
    /* pointer-events:none on inactive quotes prevents their invisible buttons from
       intercepting taps that visually land on the active quote's buttons. */
    .t-quote         { position: absolute; inset: 0; width: 100%; opacity: 0; display: block; pointer-events: none; }
    .t-quote.is-active { opacity: 1; pointer-events: auto; }
    /* Play button: in-flow inside btn-row */
    .t-play-btn {
      position: relative;
      bottom: auto;
      left: auto;
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    .t-btn-row .t-play-btn { margin-top: 0; }
  }
  /* ─── Full-story popup: quote font-size at ≤768px ─── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    :global(.t-fs-quote p) {
      font-size: 28px;
      line-height: 44px;
    }
  }

  /* ─── Full-story modal: mobile single-column restack ≤768px ─────────── */
  /* Order: quote (full width) → name & role → images                       */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    /* Switch grid → single-column flex */
    .t-fs-body {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      padding-top: 56px;
      padding-bottom: 48px;
    }

    /* Quote comes first — full width of panel */
    .t-fs-right {
      order: 1;
      padding: 0 24px 32px;
      width: 100%;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    /* Name + role + images come second */
    .t-fs-left {
      order: 2;
      padding: 0 24px 32px;
      width: 100%;
      box-sizing: border-box;
      /* Flex column already set on parent; inherit */
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    /* Images: keep vertical stack */
    .t-fs-images {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 20px;
    }

    /* Slightly smaller quote text on narrow screens */
    :global(.t-fs-quote p) {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 36px;
    }
  }

  /* ── 390px: single-column stacked testimonial layout ──────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 390px) {
    /* Tighten sticky panel vertical padding so everything fits in 100vh */
    .testimonials-sticky {
      padding: 48px 0; /* symmetrical — content stays vertically centred */
    }

    /* Reduce header / rule spacing */
    .testimonials__heading { margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .testimonials__rule    { margin-bottom: 20px; }

    /* Single-column flex — image stacked above quote */
    .testimonials__body {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0;
    }

    /* Photo: full width, fixed 238px height, object-fit:cover */
    .testimonials__photo-stage {
      width: 100%;
      height: 238px;
      aspect-ratio: unset;     /* override 768px aspect-ratio: 2/3 */
      min-height: unset;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    /* Swap carousel portraits: hide desktop image, show mobile image */
    .t-photo img.t-photo__img--desktop { display: none; }
    .t-photo img.t-photo__img--mobile  { display: block; }

    /* Quote stage: full width, explicit height so position:absolute
       crossfade children have a stable containing block — nothing
       reflows when the carousel cycles through testimonials */
    .testimonials__quote-stage {
      width: 100%;
      height: 400px;
      min-height: unset;       /* override 768px min-height: 500px */
      margin-right: 0;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    /* Quote text: 20px / 1.6, 8-line clamp.
       !important beats the late-cascade 768px rule (font-size: 28px !important)
       because this block comes later in the stylesheet. */
    .t-quote blockquote {
      font-size: 20px !important;
      line-height: 30px !important;
      -webkit-line-clamp: 8;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    /* Paul Amadi (index 5): one line fewer — quote is shorter so it
       ends naturally with closing ” rather than hitting the clamp */
    .t-quote[data-index="5"] blockquote {
      -webkit-line-clamp: 7;
    }

    /* Attribution spacing */
    .t-attribution {
      margin-top: 12px;
    }

    /* CTA — full width, centred */
    .t-story-btn {
      display: flex;
      width: 100%;
      justify-content: center;
      box-sizing: border-box;
